Design

AIM: 10-20 candidate spacers, 20 nt length

Criteria Details Evaluation Done

Sensitivity

Activity against SARS-CoV-2, accounting for genomic diversity

Compute %detected, allow for 0 or 1 mismatches

x

Specificity

Low activity against other human coronaviruses

Compute %missed, allow 2 mismatches

x

Low activity against off-targets (human, cow, co-occuring pathogens)

Align to transcriptomes, allow 2 mismatches (FDA requirement: <80% homology [≥4 mismatches])

!

Good Cas12 guide

PAM sequence constraint

Select TTTN PAM sequence ; flag if PAM is TTTT

x

RNA secondary structure

High minimum folding energy of spacer ; low base-pairing with crRNA hairpin ; low base-pairing in spacer seed

x

GC content

Flag if GC content not between 20-50%

x

Good viral target

RNA abundance

Prioritize highly abundant subgenomic regions

Selection of target window

  • Number of SARS-CoV-2 genomes: 5628
  • Number of human coronavirus genomes (list from FDA): 6
    • NC_004718.3 : SARS CoV
    • NC_019843.3 : MERS
    • NC_006213.1 : Human CoV OC43
    • NC_006577.2 : Human CoV
    • NC_002645.1 : Human CoV 229E
    • NC_005831.2 : Human CoV NL63
  • Viral abundance data set: throat swab samples from PRJNA616446

0. Select spacers with correct PAM

1. Filter out spacers that interfere with crRNA hairpin

2. Filter out spacers with >4 internal base-paired positions

3. Select spacers with 100% specificity

4. Filter out spacers with >10 alignments to human genome

5. Filter out PAM sequences that are TTTT

6. Select one spacer per overlapping window

  • Window overlap: ≥10 nt
  • Spacer prioritization:
    • Fewer alignments to human genome
    • Higher sensitivity

7. Select top 20 by sensitivity

  • Allowing 0 mismatches
